  "body": "\r\n*Description*:\r\n>Variable interpretation is now allowed for HTTP based ext_authz `headers_to_add` (see #7946), but there seems to be no way to do something similar with gRPC ext_authz services. The gRPC version has an `initial_metadata` field (see: https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/api-v2/api/v2/core/grpc_service.proto#envoy-api-msg-core-grpcservice) that seems like it could work similarly, but it does not support variable interpretation. \r\n>\r\n> I'd like to do something like the following in order to include more info on the downstream connection for auth:\r\n>```\r\n>           - name: envoy.ext_authz\r\n>             config:\r\n>               grpc_service:\r\n>                 envoy_grpc:\r\n>                   cluster_name: my-cluster-grpc\r\n>                 timeout: 0.2s\r\n>                 initial_metadata:\r\n>                 - key: \"x-downstream-tls-cipher\"\r\n>                   value: \"%DOWNSTREAM_TLS_CIPHER%\"\r\n>                 - key: \"x-downstream-tls-version\"\r\n>                   value: \"%DOWNSTREAM_TLS_VERSION%\"\r\n> ```\r\n>\r\n> There are also probably similar needs in other filters, such as `envoy.rate_limit` also noted in #7946 \r\n\r\ncc @dio ",
